## 📌 Overview

**Word Counter Pro** is an advanced text analysis desktop application built with Python. It goes far beyond simple word counting — it performs NLP-style analysis including readability scoring, lexical diversity measurement, bigram extraction, and frequency distribution visualisation, all wrapped in a clean Tkinter GUI.

This project was built as part of my Python learning journey and serves a dual purpose:

1. **As a standalone tool** — useful for academic writers, researchers, and students who want deep insight into their documents.
2. **As a conceptual prototype** — every core technique in this project has a direct parallel in bioinformatics pipeline development, as detailed in the [Bioinformatics Bridge](#-bioinformatics-bridge) section below.

---

## ✨ Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| 📂 Multi-format file support | Reads `.txt`, `.pdf`, and `.docx` files |
| 📊 Word frequency analysis | Top-N most frequent words with stopword removal |
| 🔗 Bigram extraction | Identifies meaningful two-word phrases |
| 📖 Readability scoring | Flesch-Kincaid score with reading level classification |
| 🧠 Lexical diversity | Unique word ratio as a vocabulary richness metric |
| 📝 Document statistics | Word count, sentence count, paragraph count, average lengths |
| 📈 Visualisations | Bar chart and Zipf's Law frequency distribution (Matplotlib) |
| 💾 CSV export | Structured export of word and bigram frequencies |
| 🌐 HTML report | Styled, self-contained analysis report for sharing |
| ⚡ Threaded analysis | Background processing keeps the GUI responsive |

